cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on the evaluation of context-sensitive word embeddings. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the limitations of existing word embedding techniques and proposes a new dataset for evaluation. Additionally, it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the development of intelligent systems for natural language understanding. It may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as word embeddings are often used in information retrieval tasks, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are commonly used in the development of word embedding models.
